{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017dt9o9e29hGrLXuSP2A4jC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package spring.tutorial.roster;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     5→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     6→import org.springframework.boot.test.context.SpringBootTest;\n     7→import org.springframework.test.annotation.DirtiesContext;\n     8→import spring.tutorial.roster.request.Request;\n     9→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n    10→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.PlayerDetails;\n    11→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n    12→\n    13→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;\n    14→\n    15→@SpringBootTest\n    16→@DirtiesContext(classMode = DirtiesContext.ClassMode.AFTER_EACH_TEST_METHOD)\n    17→class RequestQueriesIT {\n    18→\n    19→  @Autowired\n    20→  Request request;\n    21→\n    22→  @Test\n    23→  void queryScenarios() {\n    24→    request.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"Lq\",\"Summer\",\"soccer\"));\n    25→    request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"Tq\",\"Tigers\",\"Austin\"), \"Lq\");\n    26→    request.createPlayer(\"Pa\",\"Alice\",\"Forward\",100);\n    27→    request.createPlayer(\"Pb\",\"Bob\",\"Goalie\",120);\n    28→    request.createPlayer(\"Pz\",\"Zed\",\"Forward\",90);\n    29→    request.addPlayer(\"Pa\",\"Tq\");\n    30→    request.addPlayer(\"Pb\",\"Tq\");\n    31→\n    32→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersByPosition(\"Forward\")).containsAll(List.of(\"Pa\",\"Pz\")));\n    33→    assertEquals(List.of(\"Pb\"), ids(request.getPlayersByHigherSalary(\"Alice\")));\n    34→    assertEquals(List.of(\"Pa\"), ids(request.getPlayersBySalaryRange(95,110)));\n    35→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersByLeagueId(\"Lq\")).containsAll(List.of(\"Pa\",\"Pb\")));\n    36→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersBySport(\"soccer\")).containsAll(List.of(\"Pa\",\"Pb\")));\n    37→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersByCity(\"Austin\")).containsAll(List.of(\"Pa\",\"Pb\")));\n    38→    assertTrue(ids(request.getPlayersNotOnTeam()).contains(\"Pz\"));\n    39→    assertEquals(List.of(\"Pa\"), ids(request.getPlayersByPositionAndName(\"Forward\",\"Alice\")));\n    40→    assertEquals(List.of(\"Lq\"), request.getLeaguesOfPlayer(\"Pa\").stream().map(LeagueDetails::getId).toList());\n    41→    assertTrue(request.getSportsOfPlayer(\"Pa\").contains(\"soccer\"));\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  private static List<String> ids(List<PlayerDetails> list) {\n    45→    return list.stream().map(PlayerDetails::getId).toList();\n    46→  }\n    47→}\n    48→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2c11cb83-6ba2-4880-b8f2-f05df9ef97a7","uuid":"a74d4890-e1c0-4bab-88bd-9765a642f207"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y7uCL5HiMqo2xyfPYDem4Q","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package spring.tutorial.roster;\n     2→\n     3→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     4→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     5→import org.springframework.boot.test.context.SpringBootTest;\n     6→import org.springframework.test.annotation.DirtiesContext;\n     7→import spring.tutorial.roster.request.Request;\n     8→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n     9→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n    10→\n    11→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;\n    12→\n    13→@SpringBootTest\n    14→@DirtiesContext(classMode = DirtiesContext.ClassMode.AFTER_EACH_TEST_METHOD)\n    15→class RequestCrudIT {\n    16→\n    17→  @Autowired\n    18→  Request request;\n    19→\n    20→  @Test\n    21→  void leagueTeamPlayerCrud() {\n    22→    request.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"Lx\",\"LX\",\"soccer\"));\n    23→    request.createTeamInLeague(new TeamDetails(\"Tx\",\"Tigers\",\"Austin\"), \"Lx\");\n    24→    request.createPlayer(\"Px\",\"Alice\",\"Forward\",100.0);\n    25→    request.addPlayer(\"Px\",\"Tx\");\n    26→\n    27→    assertEquals(1, request.getPlayersOfTeam(\"Tx\").size());\n    28→    assertNotNull(request.getTeam(\"Tx\"));\n    29→    assertNotNull(request.getLeague(\"Lx\"));\n    30→\n    31→    request.removeTeam(\"Tx\");\n    32→    assertEquals(0, request.getTeamsOfLeague(\"Lx\").size());\n    33→    assertEquals(0, request.getPlayersOfTeam(\"Tx\").size());\n    34→\n    35→    request.removeLeague(\"Lx\");\n    36→    assertNull(request.getLeague(\"Lx\"));\n    37→\n    38→    request.removePlayer(\"Px\");\n    39→    assertNull(request.getPlayer(\"Px\"));\n    40→    assertEquals(0, request.getAllPlayers().size());\n    41→  }\n    42→}\n    43→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2c11cb83-6ba2-4880-b8f2-f05df9ef97a7","uuid":"7c6e4a41-aa2b-4697-9c7f-6b1fa5285d6c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WHmYP9pcZAaVe5Eeup1J3P","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package spring.tutorial.roster;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Optional;\n     4→import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     5→import org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.ExtendWith;\n     6→import org.mockito.ArgumentCaptor;\n     7→import org.mockito.junit.jupiter.MockitoExtension;\n     8→import org.mockito.Mock;\n     9→import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;\n    10→import static org.mockito.Mockito.*;\n    11→import spring.tutorial.roster.request.RequestBean;\n    12→import spring.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n    13→import spring.tutorial.roster.repository.LeagueRepository;\n    14→import spring.tutorial.roster.repository.PlayerRepository;\n    15→import spring.tutorial.roster.repository.TeamRepository;\n    16→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.League;\n    17→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.Player;\n    18→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.SummerLeague;\n    19→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.Team;\n    20→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.WinterLeague;\n    21→\n    22→@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)\n    23→class RequestBeanUnitTest {\n    24→\n    25→  @Mock PlayerRepository playerRepository;\n    26→  @Mock TeamRepository teamRepository;\n    27→  @Mock LeagueRepository leagueRepository;\n    28→\n    29→  @Test\n    30→  void createLeagueChoosesSeasonType() {\n    31→    RequestBean bean = new RequestBean(playerRepository, teamRepository, leagueRepository);\n    32→\n    33→    bean.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"L1\",\"Name\",\"soccer\"));\n    34→    ArgumentCaptor<League> cap1 = ArgumentCaptor.forClass(League.class);\n    35→    verify(leagueRepository).save(cap1.capture());\n    36→    assertTrue(cap1.getValue() instanceof SummerLeague);\n    37→\n    38→    reset(leagueRepository);\n    39→    bean.createLeague(new LeagueDetails(\"L2\",\"Name\",\"hockey\"));\n    40→    ArgumentCaptor<League> cap2 = ArgumentCaptor.forClass(League.class);\n    41→    verify(leagueRepository).save(cap2.capture());\n    42→    assertTrue(cap2.getValue() instanceof WinterLeague);\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  @Test\n    46→  void addPlayerLinksAndSavesTeam() {\n    47→    RequestBean bean = new RequestBean(playerRepository, teamRepository, leagueRepository);\n    48→    Player p = new Player(\"P1\",\"Alice\",\"Forward\",100);\n    49→    Team t = new Team(\"T1\",\"Tigers\",\"Austin\");\n    50→    when(playerRepository.findById(\"P1\")).thenReturn(Optional.of(p));\n    51→    when(teamRepository.findById(\"T1\")).thenReturn(Optional.of(t));\n    52→\n    53→    bean.addPlayer(\"P1\",\"T1\");\n    54→\n    55→    verify(teamRepository).save(t);\n    56→    assertTrue(t.getPlayers().contains(p));\n    57→    assertTrue(p.getTeams().contains(t));\n    58→  }\n    59→}\n    60→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2c11cb83-6ba2-4880-b8f2-f05df9ef97a7","uuid":"54469f4e-7bdb-46e3-b70d-3c0f70a90253"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014bhLtYFxwukcNcnpmbiuKL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me plan the migration strategy. The key changes needed:\n\n**Spring → Quarkus Migration Plan:**\n1. Multi-module project with `roster-common` (plain Java) and `roster-boot` (Spring Boot) \n2. Spring Data JPA repositories → Quarkus Panache repositories (or manual EntityManager-based repos)\n3. `@SpringBootApplication` → Quarkus (no main class needed, or use `@QuarkusMain`)\n4. `@RestController/@RequestMapping` → JAX-RS `@Path/@GET/@POST` etc.\n5. `@Service/@Transactional` → CDI `@ApplicationScoped` + `@Transactional` from Jakarta\n6. Spring Data repository interfaces → Manual repository implementations using EntityManager\n7. `application.properties` → Quarkus format\n8. Dockerfile CMD → Quarkus runner\n\nLet me start the migration. I'll consolidate the multi-module project into a single module for Quarkus since the roster-common module is just POJOs and an interface."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3173,"cache_read_input_tokens":40085,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3173,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":784},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2c11cb83-6ba2-4880-b8f2-f05df9ef97a7","uuid":"8c8f7cb1-0dcb-403a-8a32-44ffee450d05"}
