{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PoUDCzcZmHxQ2ub2iLnsAN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# VCS\n     2→.git/\n     3→\n     4→# Maven\n     5→.mvn/\n     6→**/.mvn/\n     7→mvnw\n     8→mvnw.cmd\n     9→**/mvnw\n    10→**/mvnw.cmd\n    11→target/\n    12→**/target/\n    13→pom.xml.tag\n    14→pom.xml.releaseBackup\n    15→pom.xml.versionsBackup\n    16→pom.xml.next\n    17→release.properties\n    18→dependency-reduced-pom.xml\n    19→buildNumber.properties\n    20→\n    21→# IDE / Editor\n    22→.vscode/\n    23→**/.vscode/\n    24→.zed/\n    25→**/.zed/\n    26→.idea/\n    27→**/.idea/\n    28→*.iml\n    29→*.ipr\n    30→*.iws\n    31→\n    32→# OS\n    33→.DS_Store\n    34→**/.DS_Store\n    35→Thumbs.db\n    36→ehthumbs.db\n    37→\n    38→# Logs / temp\n    39→*.log\n    40→*.tmp\n    41→*.temp\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2c11cb83-6ba2-4880-b8f2-f05df9ef97a7","uuid":"9f2b0314-561c-4cba-98ca-c3607929020b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01J2vqRbuBQvVkSxHgar9i4M","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me create the new project structure. For Quarkus, I'll flatten into a single module. The key decision is that Quarkus uses the `quarkus-hibernate-orm-panache` extension approach, but since the Spring Data repositories use complex derived query methods, I'll use `quarkus-spring-data-jpa` extension for compatibility (Quarkus has Spring compatibility extensions), OR I'll manually implement using EntityManager + JPQL. \n\nActually, the cleanest Quarkus migration would be to use Quarkus's Spring compatibility extensions which allow Spring Data JPA repositories and Spring Web annotations to work. But that's not a real migration - just a compatibility shim. For a proper migration, I'll use JAX-RS + CDI + Hibernate ORM with EntityManager/Panache.\n\nLet me create all the new files:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":517,"cache_read_input_tokens":48220,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":517,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":420},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2c11cb83-6ba2-4880-b8f2-f05df9ef97a7","uuid":"95cb51b1-513f-432c-a18f-affb371f8a01"}
